The paper discusses a payment mechanism for incentivizing workers in crowdsourcing to provide high-quality data. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves using human input to train machine learning models. The paper also discusses the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect of crowdsourcing and the potential for spamming (cs.CY). Finally, the paper presents experimental results (cs.SI) to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed mechanism.
